s^-1 · m^1.name: metre per second
s^-1 · m^1.description: Measures the rate of change of position with respect to time.

s^-2 · m^1.name: metre per second squared
s^-2 · m^1.description: Measures the rate of change of velocity with respect to time.

m^-1.name: reciprocal metre
m^-1.description: Measures the spatial frequency of a wave.
examples: Wave number of a sound wave

m^-3 · kg^1.name: kilogram per cubic metre
m^-3 · kg^1.description: Measures the mass per unit volume of a substance.
examples: Density of water, Density of air

m^-2 · kg^1.name: kilogram per square metre
m^-2 · kg^1.description: Measures the mass per unit area of a surface.
examples: Mass per unit area of a sheet of paper, Mass per unit area of a thin film

m^3 · kg^-1.name: cubic metre per kilogram
m^3 · kg^-1.description: Measures the volume occupied by a unit mass of a substance.
examples: Specific volume of steam, Specific volume of liquid water

m^-2 · A^1.name: ampere per square metre
m^-2 · A^1.description: Measures the electric current flowing through a unit area.
m^-2 · A^1.examples: Current density in a wire, Current density in a semiconductor

m^-1 · A^1.name: ampere per metre
m^-1 · A^1.description: Measures the strength of a magnetic field.
m^-1 · A^1.examples: Magnetic field strength inside a solenoid, Magnetic field strength of the Earth

m^-3 · mol^1.name: mole per cubic metre
m^-3 · mol^1.description: Measures the amount of substance per unit volume of a solution.
m^-3 · mol^1.examples: Concentration of a salt solution, Concentration of a gas in air

m^-2 · cd^1.name: candela per square metre
m^-2 · cd^1.description: Measures the luminous intensity per unit projected area of a surface.
m^-2 · cd^1.examples: Luminance of a computer screen, Luminance of a light bulb

s^-1 · m^-1 · kg^1.name: pascal-second
s^-1 · m^-1 · kg^1.description: Measures the resistance of a fluid to shear stress.
s^-1 · m^-1 · kg^1.examples: Viscosity of water, Viscosity of oil

s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1.name: newton-metre
s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1.description: Measures the torque or rotational force applied to an object.
examples: Torque applied to a wrench, Torque produced by an electric motor

s^-2 · kg^1.name: newton per metre
s^-2 · kg^1.description: Measures the surface tension of a liquid.
examples: Surface tension of water, Surface tension of mercury

s^-1.name: radian per second
examples: Angular velocity of a spinning wheel, Frequency of a wave

s^-2.name: radian per second squared
examples: Angular acceleration of a rotating object

s^-3 · m^1 · kg^1 · K^-1.name: watt per metre-kelvin
s^-3 · m^1 · kg^1 · K^-1.description: Measures thermal conductivity, the ability of a material to conduct heat.
examples: Thermal conductivity of copper, Thermal conductivity of glass

s^-2 · m^-1 · kg^1.name: joule per cubic metre
s^-2 · m^-1 · kg^1.description: Measures the energy stored per unit volume.
examples: Energy density of a battery, Energy density of gasoline

s^-3 · m^1 · kg^1 · A^-1.name: volt per metre
s^-3 · m^1 · kg^1 · A^-1.description: Measures the strength of an electric field.
s^-3 · m^1 · kg^1 · A^-1.examples: Electric field between two charged plates, Electric field of a point charge

s^1 · m^-3 · A^1.name: coulomb per cubic metre
s^1 · m^-3 · A^1.description: Measures the electric charge per unit volume.
s^1 · m^-3 · A^1.examples: Charge density in a capacitor, Charge density in a conductor

s^1 · m^-2 · A^1.name: coulomb per square metre
s^1 · m^-2 · A^1.description: Measures the electric charge per unit area.
s^1 · m^-2 · A^1.examples: Charge density on a capacitor plate, Charge density on a charged sphere

s^4 · m^-3 · kg^-1 · A^2.name: farad per metre
s^4 · m^-3 · kg^-1 · A^2.description: Measures the ability of a material to store electric charge.
s^4 · m^-3 · kg^-1 · A^2.examples: Permittivity of free space, Permittivity of a dielectric material

s^-2 · m^1 · kg^1 · A^-2.name: henry per metre
s^-2 · m^1 · kg^1 · A^-2.description: Measures the ability of a material to magnetize in response to an applied magnetic field.
s^-2 · m^1 · kg^1 · A^-2.examples: Permeability of free space, Permeability of a ferromagnetic material

s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1 · K^-1 · mol^-1.name: joule per mole-kelvin
s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1 · K^-1 · mol^-1.description: Measures the entropy or heat capacity per mole of a substance.
s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1 · K^-1 · mol^-1.examples: Molar entropy of water, Molar heat capacity of iron

s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1 · mol^-1.name: joule per mole
s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1 · mol^-1.description: Measures the energy per mole of a substance.
s^-2 · m^2 · kg^1 · mol^-1.examples: Molar energy of a chemical reaction, Molar energy of a phase transition

s^1 · kg^-1 · A^1.name: coulomb per kilogram
s^1 · kg^-1 · A^1.description: Measures the amount of ionizing radiation.
s^1 · kg^-1 · A^1.examples: Exposure from X-rays, Exposure from gamma rays

s^-3 · m^2.name: gray per second
s^-3 · m^2.description: Measures the rate at which ionizing radiation is absorbed by a material.
s^-3 · m^2.examples: Dose rate from a radioactive source

s^-3 · m^2 · kg^1 · sr^-1.name: watt per steradian
s^-3 · m^2 · kg^1 · sr^-1.description: Measures the power radiated by a source per unit solid angle.
s^-3 · m^2 · kg^1 · sr^-1.examples: Radiant intensity of a laser, Radiant intensity of a light bulb

s^-3 · kg^1 · sr^-1.name: watt per square metre-steradian
s^-3 · kg^1 · sr^-1.description: Measures the radiant power emitted, reflected, transmitted or received by a surface per unit solid angle per unit projected area of the source.
s^-3 · kg^1 · sr^-1.examples: Radiance of the Sun, Radiance of a light-emitting diode

s^-1 · m^-3 · mol^1.name: katal per cubic metre
s^-1 · m^-3 · mol^1.description: Measures the catalytic activity per unit volume.
s^-1 · m^-3 · mol^1.examples: Catalytic activity of an enzyme solution

K^1.name: degree Celsius
K^1.description: Measures temperature on the Celsius scale.
K^1.examples: Temperature of a room, Temperature of boiling water

DUPLICATE A s^-2 · m^2.name: gray
DUPLICATE A s^-2 · m^2.description: Measures the amount of ionizing radiation energy absorbed per unit mass of a material.
DUPLICATE A s^-2 · m^2.examples: Dose from a medical X-ray, Dose from radiation therapy

DUPLICATE B s^-2 · m^2.name: sievert
DUPLICATE B s^-2 · m^2.description: Measures the biological effect of ionizing radiation.
DUPLICATE B s^-2 · m^2.examples: Effective dose from background radiation, Effective dose from a nuclear accident

DUPLICATE s^-1.name: becquerel
DUPLICATE s^-1.description: Measures the rate of radioactive decay.

DUPLICATE s^-2 · m^-1 · kg^1.name: pascal
DUPLICATE s^-2 · m^-1 · kg^1.description: Measures the force per unit area.
